    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
            <title>RANGE SHIFT CONTROL VALVE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the two nylon air lines at the air valve on the transmission (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302407">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302407" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302407" filename="../figg13/G1302407.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Disconnect Air Lines at Air Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If desired, the gear shift lever housing lever and control valve can now be removed from the
                        transmission as a unit by removing the four bolts which attach the housing to the transmission.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the two nylon air lines at the control valve on the gear shift lever (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302408">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302408" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302408" filename="../figg13/G1302408.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Disconnect Air Lines at Control Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the ball grip from the gear shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the mounting clamp and remove the control valve and mounting clamp from the
                    lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nylon air lines, sheathing and O-ring clamp from the gear shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
